        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">After receiving a copy of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4097.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Insectivorous plants</hi></ref>, Cohn sent comments about his uncertainty regarding the protoplasmic nature of aggregated masses in cells of the tentacles of <hi rend="italic">Drosera rotundifolia</hi> (common or round-leaved sundew); see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 23, letters from F. J. Cohn, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10131.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">21 August 1875</ref> and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10137.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">28 August 1875</ref>.</note>
