            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1747.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Alexander Fraustadt’s</ref> doctoral dissertation was ‘Anatomie der vegetativen Organe von Dionaea muscipula Ell.’ (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9016.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Fraustadt 1876</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">The drawings appear as plates with <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9016.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Fraustadt 1876</ref>. CD’s annotated copy is in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">Droseraceae is a family of carnivorous plants that includes the genera <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Dionaea</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">Aldrovanda</hi>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">Cohn 1876a; a lightly annotated copy is in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL.</note>
        </div>        
            
